Problem Statement :
     Write a java program to take array length as input from user and
     create an integer array Take elements from user and store elements
     into the array Call a method printArray() present in PrintArray class
     which will print the array in forward direction and in reverse
     direction.
  Note: Use each loop for printing in forward direction.
  
 Explanation :
 	We will be creating an array of length given by the user. And storing the elements in the array as 
 	user input. By invoking a method which will be performing all the required operations as follows.
 	As parameters the array is passed to the method, and Displaying the array in forward direction and 
 	also Displaying the array in Reverse direction.
 	